Moldova, acting to defuse one of the Soviet union's most explosive ethnic conflicts, agreed to comply with a Kremlin order to reconsider its law making Moldavian the republic's official language.
Gorbachev gave the republic 10 days to dissolve a new national guard and to establish measures guaranteeing equal rights for all ethnic groups within its borders.
Unrest has griped Moldava, a largely agricultural republic bordering Romania, during its push for independence from the Soviet Union.
Alarmed by rising Moldavian nationalism and declaring they are discriminated against by Moldavans, two of the republic's minority groups have begun their own separatist movements. 
